No widget should contain hardcoded colors.

---

# Typography

Create a centralized typography system.

Support:

* Display Large
* Display Medium
* Display Small
* Headline
* Title
* Body
* Label

All text colors should come from ThemeData.

Never manually assign Colors.black or Colors.white.

---

# Buttons

Support all button types:

* FilledButton
* ElevatedButton
* OutlinedButton
* TextButton
* IconButton
* FloatingActionButton

Buttons should automatically adapt to the active theme.

---

# Cards & Containers

Every Card and Container should automatically use:

* correct background
* border
* shadow
* elevation
* radius

No duplicated decoration code.

---

# Icons

Icons should automatically switch colors.

Support:

* active
* inactive
* disabled
* warning
* success
* error

---

# Images

Support:

* Light Logo
* Dark Logo
* Light SVG
* Dark SVG
* Light Illustrations
* Dark Illustrations

Automatically switch assets based on the active theme.

---

# Gradients

Create reusable gradients.

Examples:

* Primary
* Success
* Error
* Premium
* Gold
* Purple
* Green
* Blue

Dark mode should have its own optimized gradients.

---

# Theme Extension

Use ThemeExtension for custom:

* Colors
* Gradients
* Shadows
* Borders
* Card Styles

Do not hardcode custom colors anywhere.

---

# Reusable Widgets

Update every reusable widget.

Examples:

* AppButton
* GradientButton
* AppText
* AppCard
* ProfileTile
* SettingsTile
* ChatBubble
* SubscriptionCard
* ProductCard
* LoadingWidget
* ErrorWidget
* EmptyWidget
* SearchField
* OTPField
* AudioPlayer
* VideoPlayer
* Bottom Sheets
* Dialogs

Every widget must read colors from Theme.of(context).

---

# Animation

Animate theme switching.

Requirements:

* AnimatedTheme
* 300–500ms transition
* Smooth color interpolation
* No screen flickering

---

# Settings Screen

Create a Theme Settings screen.

Include:

* Light Mode
* Dark Mode
* System Default

Display the current selection.

Persist changes immediately.

---

# Performance

Optimize rebuilds using Riverpod best practices.

* Avoid unnecessary widget rebuilds.
* Use ref.watch() only where needed.
* Use ref.read() for actions.
* Keep providers granular.
* Prefer immutable state.

---

# Code Quality

Follow:

* SOLID principles
* Clean Architecture
* Feature-first folder structure
* Reusable widgets
* Null safety
* Dart best practices
* Material 3 guidelines

Avoid duplicate code.

---

# Deliverables

Provide complete production-ready code for:

* ThemeState
* ThemeNotifier
* ThemeProvider
* ThemeService
* AppTheme
* LightTheme
* DarkTheme
* AppColors
* AppGradients
* ThemeExtension
* SharedPreferences integration
* main.dart setup
* Riverpod initialization
* Theme settings page
* Theme toggle widget
* Example screens

The implementation should be scalable enough to support future themes (e.g., AMOLED, Blue Theme, Green Theme, High Contrast) with minimal code changes.
